The difference in plain terms

Faith + confidence (through action)

* Built on doing, not declaring
* Updated by feedback (“what actually happened?”)
* Stays flexible—can pivot when reality disagrees
* Quietly accumulates evidence

Pride

* Built on identity (“I’m right / I’ve arrived”)
* Resists disconfirming feedback
* Locks you into a position
* Seeks validation more than signal

⸻

A clean test you can use in the moment

Ask:

“If this fails, do I update—or defend?”

* Update → you’re in faith/confidence
* Defend → you’ve slipped into pride

